<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1759,2025]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,152,458]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1759,1785]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[727,871,1759,1785]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.6">2.6–2.9 mm</quantity>
. General color, in alcohol, pale brown; head and thorax with golden setae, antennae light yellow, legs pale brown with dark brown setae, wings pale brown with brown setae. Male genitalia. Sternum IX short, with deep incision U-shaped in anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1421,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1421,1839,1865]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergum X membranous, divided mesally in 
<number box="[671,686,1879,1905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
lobes covered by long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1181,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
). Preanal appendages with dorsolateral lobes short, broad and oblong, with long setae (
<figureCitation box="[935,1082,1919,1945]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
); and with ventromesal lobes simple, bent, and apices narrowed, gradually darkened, and curved laterad (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1180,1959,1985]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Figs. 17, 18</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages elongate, apically dark, each with internal apical face straight; its basodorsal lobe reaching apex of main body of appendage, strongly sclerotized, depressed, bearing four spine-like setae on internal surface, apically truncate with short apicomesal projection (
<figureCitation box="[612,758,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Figs. 17, 19</figureCitation>
). Phallus tubular, short, with apicodorsal area depressed; internally with 
<number box="[332,347,232,258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
long dark spines posteriorly, and phallicata sclerite with ventral semicircular piece and pair of oval plates dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[426,514,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1920,1944]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,517,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Cernotina flexuosa sp. nov. (17) male genitalia, left lateral; (18) tergum X, and preanal appendages, dorsal; (19) sternum IX, and inferior appendages, ventral. (20) phallus, left lateral. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[481,514,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,311,337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint, 1971" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1971" box="[749,1124,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cernotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[749,983,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Cernotina filiformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint" box="[992,1124,312,338]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" refString="Flint, O. S., Jr. (1971) Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XII: Rhyacophilidae, Glossosomatidae, Philopotamidae, and Psychomyiidae from the Amazon basin (Trichoptera). Amazoniana, 3, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1971">
Flint, 
<number box="[1063,1124,312,338]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly in the shapes of the ventromesal lobes of the preanal appendages and tergum X. 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1166,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cernotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[941,1166,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">Cernotina flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1174,1268,351,377]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1174,1268,351,377]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[313,455,392,418]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Cernotina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[313,332,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[348,455,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="32">filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the free, strongly sclerotized, and apically truncate basodorsal lobe of each inferior appendage; and by the phallus bearing 
<number box="[658,673,432,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
long straight spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184498/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="32" targetBox="[176,1411,543,1875]" targetPageId="7">
